=\"ico-pdf\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-pdf\"></use></svg>Download PDF</span><div class=\"dropdown-menu zDocsDropdownMenu\"><a class=\"zDocsExportItem zDocsExportTopicButton\" href=\"#\" id=\"singlePdf\" role=\"button\">Save selected topic</a><a class=\"zDocsExportItem zDocsExportSubtopicsButton\" href=\"#\" id=\"pdfWithChildren\" role=\"button\">Save selected topic and subtopics</a><a class=\"zDocsExportItem zDocsExportBundleButton\" href=\"#\" id=\"wholeBundlePdf\" role=\"button\">Save entire publication</a></div></div><div class=\"zDocsTopicShare zDocsShareButton\" role=\"listitem\"><span aria-expanded=\"false\" aria-label=\"Share\" class=\"d-none d-lg-flex zDocsShareDialogButton\" data-toggle=\"dropdown\" data-tooltip-content=\"Share\" data-tooltip-id=\"zDocsTopicActionsTooltip\" role=\"button\" tabindex=\"0\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-share\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-share\"></use></svg></span><span class=\"d-lg-none zDocsShareDialogButton\" role=\"button\" tabindex=\"0\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-share\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-share\"></use></svg>Share</span><div class=\"dropdown-menu zDocsDropdownMenu\"><a class=\"dropdown-item zDocsShareButton zDocsShareEmail\" href=\"#\" role=\"button\"><span>Email Link</span></a><a class=\"dropdown-item zDocsShareButton zDocsShareLink\" href=\"#\" role=\"button\"><span>Copy Link</span></a></div></div><div class=\"zDocsFeedback zDocsFeedback zDocsTopicFeedback\" role=\"listitem\"><span aria-label=\"Feedback\" class=\"zDocsFeedbackButton d-none d-lg-flex\" data-backdrop=\"static\" data-target=\"#feedbackModal_main_5613394\" data-toggle=\"modal\" data-tooltip-content=\"Feedback\" data-tooltip-id=\"zDocsTopicActionsTooltip\" role=\"button\" tabindex=\"0\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-feedback\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-feedback\"></use></svg></span><span class=\"d-lg-none d-flex zDocsFeedbackButton\" data-backdrop=\"static\" data-return-focus=\"#zDocsTopicActionsMobile\" data-target=\"#feedbackModal_main_5613394\" data-toggle=\"modal\" role=\"button\" tabindex=\"0\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-feedback\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-feedback\"></use></svg><span class=\"zDocsFeedbackButtonText\"> Feedback</span></span></div></div><div class=\"zDocsTopicActionsMobile\"><button aria-label=\"Show topic actions\" data-toggle=\"dropdown\" id=\"zDocsTopicActionsMobile\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-ellipsis-h\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-ellipsis-h\"></use></svg></button><div class=\"dropdown-menu zDocsDropdownMenu zDocsTopicActionsMobileDropdown dropdown-menu-right\"></div></div><div style=\"flex-basis: 100%; height: 0px;\"></div><ul class=\"zDocsTopicPageDetails\"><li class=\"zDocsTopicPageDate css-cinqea\">Last Updated<span class=\"css-cinqea\">Apr 30, 2025</span></li><li class=\"zDocsAiTopicSummaryDetailsItem\"><button class=\"zDocsAiTopicSummaryButton\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-topic-summary\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-topic-summary\"></use></svg>Summarize</button></li><li class=\"spacer\" role=\"presentation\"></li><div class=\"zDocsLabelWrapper\"><ul><li class=\"zDocsLabel\"><a aria-describedby=\"hyperLinkFacetsTooltip\" class=\"css-ettsdk\" data-tooltip-content=\"Search all site by tag: Uniface\" data-tooltip-id=\"hyperLinkFacetsTooltip\" href=\"/de-DE/search?labelkey=prod_uniface\" stylesprops=\"[object Object]\"><svg aria-label=\"Tag\" class=\"ico-tag\" role=\"img\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-tag\"></use></svg>Uniface</a></li><li class=\"zDocsLabel\"><a aria-describedby=\"hyperLinkFacetsTooltip\" class=\"css-ettsdk\" data-tooltip-content=\"Search all site by tag: 10.4\" data-tooltip-id=\"hyperLinkFacetsTooltip\" href=\"/de-DE/search?labelkey=uniface_10.4\" stylesprops=\"[object Object]\"><svg aria-label=\"Tag\" class=\"ico-tag\" role=\"img\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-tag\"></use></svg>10.4</a></li></ul></div></ul></header><div class=\"zDocsTopicPageBody\" data-prismjs-copy=\"Copy\" data-prismjs-copy-error=\"Copy failed! Use Ctrl + C instead.\" data-prismjs-copy-success=\"Copied!\"><div class=\"zDocsTopicPageBodyContent wide\" dir=\"ltr\"><div id=\"zDocsAiSummaryContaineruniface_104ecs1703254253418.html\"></div><div><article class=\"hascomments\" data-page=\"bundle:uniface_104/enus/ecs1703254253418.html\" id=\"bundle:uniface_104/enus/ecs1703254253418.html\"><main role=\"main\"><article aria-labelledby=\"ariaid-title1\" class=\"dita\" id=\"pwi1665702658109\" role=\"article\">\n<h1 class=\"title topictitle1\" id=\"ariaid-title1\">\n      Default Key Combinations\n </h1>\n<div class=\"body conbody\"><p class=\"shortdesc\">A complete set of keystroke combinations is available in all the keyboard translation tables supplied in the USYS library. These keystroke combinations are defined by the macro <code class=\"ph codeph\">^GOLD_BASE_SET</code> and are the same for every keyboard, unless they are not defined in the keyboard translation table being used. These, or default mappings of your own, should be included in any keyboard translation table you create.\n </p>\n<p class=\"p\" id=\"pwi1665702658109__p_d64409e1_d64410e1_d64411e1\">The macro <code class=\"ph codeph\">^GOLD_BASE_SET</code> includes the following definitions:</p>\n<ul class=\"ul\">\n<li class=\"li\" id=\"pwi1665702658109__li_d27872e1_d27873e1_d27874e1\">Subfield separator\n </li>\n<li class=\"li\" id=\"pwi1665702658109__li_d27875e1_d27876e1_d27877e1\">Profile characters\n </li>\n<li class=\"li\" id=\"pwi1665702658109__li_d27878e1_d27879e1_d27880e1\">Gold key combinations that allow keyboard entry of simple structure editor functions\n </li>\n<li class=\"li\" id=\"pwi1665702658109__li_d27881e1_d27882e1_d27883e1\">Super key (by default, <span class=\"ph keypress\">Gold</span>\n<span class=\"ph keypress\">Space</span>)\n </li>\n<li class=\"li\" id=\"pwi1665702658109__li_d27884e1_d27885e1_d27886e1\">Super key combinations that allow keyboard entry composite structure editor functions\n <div class=\"code-toolbar\"><pre class=\"pre language-plaintext\" tabindex=\"0\"><code class=\"language-plaintext\">HT ^FIELD\nSOH ^REFRESH\n</code></pre><div class=\"toolbar\"><div class=\"toolbar-item\"><button class=\"copy-to-clipboard-button\" data-copy-state=\"copy\" type=\"button\"><span>Copy</span></button></div></div></div>\n</li>\n</ul>\n<p class=\"p\" id=\"pwi1665702658109__p_d64412e1_d64413e1_d64414e1\">The availability of these combinations allows relative keyboard independence (once you have located the Gold key) and is especially useful if you regularly use different terminals.</p>\n<p class=\"p\" id=\"pwi1665702658109__p_d64415e1_d64416e1_d64417e1\">In your own keyboard translation tables, you should first map the location of the Gold key, then use the macro <code class=\"ph codeph\">^GOLD_BASE_SET</code> to define the complete set of keystroke combinations in one mapping. If the Gold key has not been defined when you use <code class=\"ph codeph\">^GOLD_BASE_SET</code>, the compilation fails.</p>\n<p class=\"p\" id=\"pwi1665702658109__p_d64418e1_d64419e1_d64420e1\">To include only some of the keystroke combinations\n                        defined by <code class=\"ph codeph\">^Gold_BASE_SET</code>, either disable the ones you\n                        prefer not to use or define only the ones you need. </p>\n<p class=\"p\">Example to disable the key combinations for <code class=\"ph codeph\">erase</code> in the MSWINX\n                        keyboard translation table:</p>\n<ul class=\"ul\" id=\"pwi1665702658109__ul_wgp_zpf_2fc\">\n<li class=\"li\">Ensure that the MSWINX keyboard translation table ^136+ and ^131^101 are\n                                mapped to GOLD key.</li>\n<li class=\"li\">In the MSWINX keyboard translation table, at the bottom\n                                add:<div class=\"zDocsCodeExplanationContainer\"><button aria-label=\"Explain this code\" class=\"zDocsAiActionsButton\" data-target=\"#zDocsCodeExplanationModal_uniface_104ecs1703254253418_html_0\" data-toggle=\"modal\" tabindex=\"0\" type=\"button\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-code-explanation\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-code-explanation\"></use></svg>Explain this code</button></div><div class=\"code-toolbar\"><pre class=\"pre codeblock language-plaintext\" data-explanation-rendered=\"true\" id=\"pwi1665702658109__codeblock_zlx_xpf_2fc\" tabindex=\"0\"><code class=\"language-plaintext\">^130E ^NUL\n^130e ^NUL\n^136+E ^NUL\n^131^101E ^NUL\n^136+e ^NUL\n^131^101e ^NUL</code></pre><div class=\"toolbar\"><div class=\"toolbar-item\"><button class=\"copy-to-clipboard-button\" data-copy-state=\"copy\" type=\"button\"><span>Copy</span></button></div></div></div>\n</li>\n</ul>\n<p class=\"p\">For more information, see <a class=\"xref\" data-bundleid=\"uniface_104\" data-navpath=\"ivf1703097522105.html\" href=\"/de-DE/bundle/uniface_104/page/ivf1703097522105.html\" title=\"Gold and Super key combinations are defined with ^GOLD_BASE_SET. By default, these key combinations are available in all keyboard translation tables in the USYS library that support a Gold key.\">Gold and Super Key Combinations</a>.</p>\n<p class=\"p\" id=\"pwi1665702658109__p_d64421e1_d64422e1_d64423e1\">To redefine the subfield separator or a profile character, you should map the new definition to the appropriate position in Font 0. For more information, see <a class=\"xref\" data-bundleid=\"uniface_104\" data-navpath=\"pan1665702658270.html\" href=\"/de-DE/bundle/uniface_104/page/pan1665702658270.html\" title=\"Uniface uses part of the reserved area of each meta character set (that is, the first 32 characters plus the last character) to store characters with special meaning within Uniface, such as subfield separators and profile characters.\">Subfield Separator and Profile Characters</a>.</p>\n<div class=\"example\">\n<p class=\"p\" id=\"pwi1665702658109__p_d64424e1_d64425e1_d64426e1\">The following example creates the complete set of Gold and SUPER key combinations, using the Escape key as Gold:</p>\n<div class=\"code-toolbar\"><pre class=\"pre language-plaintext\" tabindex=\"0\"><code class=\"language-plaintext\">^ESC ^GOLD\n^CHR ^GOLD_BASE_SET\n</code></pre><div class=\"toolbar\"><div class=\"toolbar-item\"><button class=\"copy-to-clipboard-button\" data-copy-state=\"copy\" type=\"button\"><span>Copy</span></button></div></div></div>\n<p class=\"p\" id=\"pwi1665702658109__p_d64427e1_d64428e1_d64429e1\">By default, the SUPER key is mapped to Gold SPACE. If you prefer, you can define the SUPER key as a single key, such as a function key. For example, on a VT200-compatible keyboard, to change the definition for the SUPER key to PF9, define the following:</p>\n<div class=\"code-toolbar\"><pre class=\"pre language-plaintext\" tabindex=\"0\"><code class=\"language-plaintext\">^CHR ^GOLD_BASE_SET\n^esc[20~ ^SUPER\n</code></pre><div class=\"toolbar\"><div class=\"toolbar-item\"><button class=\"copy-to-clipboard-button\" data-copy-state=\"copy\" type=\"button\"><span>Copy</span></button></div></div></div>\n<p class=\"p\" id=\"pwi1665702658109__p_d64430e1_d64431e1_d64432e1\">To use Gold / instead of Gold Space on an NCD keyboard, define:</p>\n<div class=\"code-toolbar\"><pre class=\"pre language-plaintext\" tabindex=\"0\"><code class=\"language-plaintext\">^CHR ^GOLD_BASE_SET\n^ESCOk/ ^SUPER\n</code></pre><div class=\"toolbar\"><div class=\"toolbar-item\"><button class=\"copy-to-clipboard-button\" data-copy-state=\"copy\" type=\"button\"><span>Copy</span></button></div></div></div>\n</div>\n</div>\n</article></main></article>\n</div></div></div><div class=\"bottomFeedback\"><div aria-labelledby=\"bottomFeedbackText\" class=\"bottomFeedbackContent\" role=\"group\"><span class=\"bottomFeedbackText\" id=\"bottomFeedbackText\">Was this topic helpful?</span><div class=\"bottomFeedbackButtonGroup\"><a data-backdrop=\"static\" data-target=\"#feedbackModal_bottom_5613394\" data-toggle=\"modal\" href=\"#\" role=\"button\" type=\"button\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-thumbs-up\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-thumbs-up\"></use></svg><span>Like</span></a><a data-backdrop=\"static\" data-target=\"#feedbackModal_bottom_5613394\" data-toggle=\"modal\" href=\"#\" role=\"button\" type=\"button\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-thumbs-down\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-thumbs-down\"></use></svg><span>Dislike</span></a></div></div></div><div style=\"position: fixed; bottom: 170px; right: 70px; cursor: pointer; transition-duration: 0.2s; transition-timing-function: linear; transition-delay: 0s; z-index: 3; opacity: 0; visibility: hidden; transition-property: opacity, visibility;\"><button aria-label=\"Scroll to top\" class=\"zDocsScrollTopBtn\" data-tooltip-content=\"Scroll to top\" data-tooltip-id=\"zDocsBackToTopToolTip\" id=\"zDocsScrollToTop\" type=\"button\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-next\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-next\"></use></svg></button></div></body></html>", "text": "Default Key Combinations Add to My Topics Add selected topic and subtopics Add Topic & Subtopics with topic head Add entire publication Watch Download PDF Save selected topic Save selected topic and subtopics Save entire publication Share Email Link Copy Link Feedback Last Updated Apr 30, 2025 Summarize Uniface 10.4 Default Key Combinations A complete set of keystroke combinations is available in all the keyboard translation tables supplied in the USYS library. These keystroke combinations are defined by the macro ^GOLD_BASE_SET and are the same for every keyboard, unless they are not defined in the keyboard translation table being used. These, or default mappings of your own, should be included in any keyboard translation table you create. The macro ^GOLD_BASE_SET includes the following definitions: Subfield separator Profile characters Gold key combinations that allow keyboard entry of simple structure editor functions Super key (by default, Gold Space ) Super key combinations that allow keyboard entry composite structure editor functions HT ^FIELD SOH ^REFRESH Copy The availability of these combinations allows relative keyboard independence (once you have located the Gold key) and is especially useful if you regularly use different terminals. In your own keyboard translation tables, you should first map the location of the Gold key, then use the macro ^GOLD_BASE_SET to define the complete set of keystroke combinations in one mapping. If the Gold key has not been defined when you use ^GOLD_BASE_SET , the compilation fails. To include only some of the keystroke combinations defined by ^Gold_BASE_SET , either disable the ones you prefer not to use or define only the ones you need. Example to disable the key combinations for erase in the MSWINX keyboard translation table: Ensure that the MSWINX keyboard translation table ^136+ and ^131^101 are mapped to GOLD key. In the MSWINX keyboard translation table, at the bottom add: Explain this code ^130E ^NUL ^130e ^NUL ^136+E ^NUL ^131^101E ^NUL ^136+e ^NUL ^131^101e ^NUL Copy For more information, see Gold and Super Key Combinations . To redefine the subfield separator or a profile character, you should map the new definition to the appropriate position in Font 0. For more information, see Subfield Separator and Profile Characters . The following example creates the complete set of Gold and SUPER key combinations, using the Escape key as Gold: ^ESC ^GOLD ^CHR ^GOLD_BASE_SET Copy By default, the SUPER key is mapped to Gold SPACE. If you prefer, you can define the SUPER key as a single key, such as a function key. For example, on a VT200-compatible keyboard, to change the definition for the SUPER key to PF9, define the following: ^CHR ^GOLD_BASE_SET ^esc[20~ ^SUPER Copy To use Gold / instead of Gold Space on an NCD keyboard, define: ^CHR ^GOLD_BASE_SET ^ESCOk/ ^SUPER Copy Was this topic helpful? Like Dislike"}